        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "To me the difference is intent. We treat\r\n\r\n```\r\nx: int\r\n```\r\nas being a Python variable because (a) a Python int and a C int aren't quite the same, and (b) we don't know that the annotation was intended for Cython - it might just have been someone documenting their code.\r\n\r\n```\r\nx = cython.declare(int)\r\n```\r\nseems pretty clearly intended for Cython (like `cdef`) so I'd treat it as a C int.",
