            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "For me cython.declare, cython.pointer etc seems like a python context (not a special cython syntax, so it may feel like we are passing python types to function)\r\nSo if we have `cython.type_x` as an argument, it should be a c type and if we have `type_x` it should be python-to-c type as in annotations.\r\n\r\nHere is an example #4298",
